Condition: What is the effect on herring?

A: Doubling fishing efforts of this type of fish species clearly decreases the size of the population of herring, as more are being caught

Condition: What is the effect on winter flounder?

A: Less fishing means the fish species has fewer predators (humans) so the population increases as it has no limiting factors

Condition: What is the effect on yellowtail flounder?

A: The population of yellowtail flounder is not affected by fishing, so decreasing the effort for catching yellowtail has no effect on their population

Condition: What is the effect on skates?

A: These fish are probably caught in large numbers when being fished, so doubling the fishing effort would dramatically reduce their population

Condition: What is the effect on cod?

A: Elasmobranchs are predators of cod, so when more elasmobranchs are being fished, their population decreases, which decreases the number of cods' predators, so their population can increase

Condition: What is the effect on haddock?

A: Haddock might feed on elasmobranchs, so when their food source is diminished, their own population decreases also

Condition: What is the effect on windowpane?

A: Windowpane may feed on elasmobranchs, so when their food source decreases, so does their population
